        id: 'confluence-merch-squad-twp-mini-plans-8',
        text: `## Guidelines for CTAs

### Journey Mapping:

Guild for trial CTAs - when to use the TwP modal, when to link direct to commerce and when to link to FTD (free trial download) pages.

[Buy-Try journey analysis and recos.pptx](https://adobe-my.sharepoint.com/:p:/p/lsogard/ERoFCewrrLRHlwui2bZ7izYB2z8Mdh_GcsbbR9UOfeJxGg?e=ZA2FoL) | [Creative Cloud Try Flows for Adobe.com](/display/adobedotcom/Creative+Cloud+Try+Flows+for+Adobe.com)

-------

### Legal Guidelines:

[Free Trial, Freemium, and Free Guidance](/display/adobedotcom/Free+Trial%2C+Freemium%2C+and+Free+Guidance)

(CONTACT LEGAL WITH QUESTIONS. Guidance is subject to change)

| Type | Payment required? | DO use: | Alt Option | Rule | DO NOT USE |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| Trial with payment | Y | Start free trial | Free trial | Must always be “free trial” phrased together regardless of what action word precedes or follows it.When buy and try buttons are together, drop "start" and just use "Free trial". | Try for freeStart for free |
| OFT/Trial without payment | N | Start free trial | Free trial | A payment method is NOT required to download and use the product or service |  |
| Freemium | N | Start nowDownload nowStart for freeDownload for freeTry for free |  | We can test this if we'd like. Other options include: “Download for free”, “Download now”, “Start now”, “Continue”, "Get started for free", "Try for free", "Start for free", "Download for free", "Get free app", "Get Adobe Express free", "Sign up for free", "Buy premium plan", "Get free plan" (only in the shared context of the premium plan - like side by side or on our plans page) | Free |`,
